                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; elements of the punctuation signs;
                           Ethiopic numerals or their elements.
 Text I
 A few lines on the
                           incipit page; names of sections occasionally followed by the feast name
                           (e.g., wāzemā za-lǝdät); names of antiphons and their abbreviations
                           occasionally followed by the feast name (e.g., mazmur za-ḥǝḍbät, śalast,
                           salām, ba-5-tu, ʾaryām, ʾabun, ʾǝsma la-ʿālam, za-yǝʾǝze, yǝtbārak);
                           names of other chants (e.g., mǝlṭān, mǝsbak, mǝqnāy, mǝdgam, qǝnnǝwat,
                           ʿǝzl za-nagh, ʿǝzl za-3 däqiq); musical notation signs: intratextual
                           (e.g., sǝräyu, qadāmi zema, qāla ʿawadi, ʾaklilä, ba-zemahu, ʿararat) and
                           marginal (entire and elements); lines separating sections and groups of
                           antiphons.
 Text II
 A few initial lines on the incipit page;
                           names of sections (wāzemā).
 Text III 
 Two initial lines of the
                           text; names of sections (zǝmmāre); abbreviations of the word ḫǝbǝst
                           “eucharistic bread”; abbreviations of the word wald “son”; musical
                           notation signs or their elements in the margin; chains of red and black
                           dots separating sections.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a: <locus from="1ra" to="8ra">1ra-8ra</locus>,
                        9ra-48vb.</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> Hand b: <locus target="#8rb">8rb-</locus>vb.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Feast names are written interlineally or in the
                              side margins: fols. 5rb, 27rb, 27va, 29rab, 29va, 35rb, 41va, 45r,
                              48rv.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>- Omitted words or passages are written in the margins, in hands a and b: e.g., fols. 3rb, 4rv, 6r, 8r, 9ra, 9v, 10vb, 12ra, 12rb, 13ra, 14rb, 15v, 16r, 16va, 17ra, 17va, 18r, 19r, 30v, 37v, 38v, 39r, 40va, 42rb, 46r, 47rv. - Tämälläs-signs, in the shape of a cross, indicating the place where the omissions, written in the margins in a secondary hand, belong: fols. 7rb l.3, 31rb l.14, 38rb l.10. - Cues for the rubricator (numerals and names written in the outer margin): fols. 20rb, 34vb, 40va, 41va. - A few lines have been erased on <locus target="#6rb">fol.  6rb</locus>. - Writing exercises: fols. 14vb, 22v, 23rv, 24v, 26v.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
